OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775902013
OL,3,CEvents unveiled to mark 100 years
OL,4,Csince the birth of Queen Elizabeth II
OL,6,FThey will mark the moment in the
OL,7,FMarble Hall of Buckingham Palace
OL,8,Falongside other members of the Royal
OL,9,FFamily and guests from a range of Her
OL,10,Flate Majesty's patronages, which
OL,11,Finclude Cancer Research UK, British
OL,12,FRed Cross Society, Jockey Club, Royal
OL,13,FKennel Club and the Army Benevolent
OL,14,FFund.
OL,16,FA day before the late Queen's
OL,17,Fbirthday, her son and daughter-in-law
OL,18,Fwill attend a new exhibition at The
OL,19,FKing's Gallery in London, which is the
OL,20,Flargest display of Elizabeth II's
OL,21,Ffashion ever mounted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
